    <innerclass refid="structstream__directory__t" prot="public">stream_directory_t</innerclass>
    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>Attach a stream-extractor to the passed stream</header>
      <description><para>These functions are used to attach a stream extractor to an already existing stream. As hinted by their names, vlc_stream_extractor_Attach will attach an <emphasis>entity-extractor</emphasis>, whereas vlc_stream_directory_Attach will attach a <emphasis>stream-directory</emphasis>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">stream</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a pointer-to-pointer to stream, <computeroutput>*stream</computeroutput> will refer to the attached stream on success, and left untouched on failure. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>identifier</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>(if present) NULL or a c-style string referring to the desired entity </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>module_name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>NULL or an explicit stream-extractor module name</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>VLC_SUCCESS if a stream-extractor was successfully attached, an error-code on failure. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</description>
      <member refid="group__stream__extractor_1ga381cd391e3daeaf71e354bb535b642a1" kind="function"><name>vlc_stream_extractor_Attach</name></member>
      <member refid="group__stream__extractor_1ga12be440a2598e9c2b6ca257127f763f2" kind="function"><name>vlc_stream_directory_Attach</name></member>
